## File Types in kohbo/

The `kohbo/` folder contains different types of files. Understanding the distinction helps with organization:

### Pages (Main Navigation)
Top-level views that appear in the navbar.
- Location: `kohbo/<section>/<section>.yaml`
- Examples: `home/home.yaml`, `security/security.yaml`, `climate/climate.yaml`
- Has `subview: false` (or omitted)

### Subviews (Detail Pages)
Pages navigated to from main pages, not directly in navbar.
- Location: `kohbo/<section>/<page>.yaml` or `kohbo/rooms/<floor>/<room>.yaml`
- Examples: `rooms/main_floor/kitchen.yaml`, `security/pages/house_locks.yaml`
- Has `subview: true`
- Typically has back navigation in toolbar

### Popups (Hash-Based Overlays)
Bubble-card popups triggered by `#hash` navigation. Can be embedded in any page.
- Location: Within page files OR in `kohbo/shared/` for reusable popups
- Examples: `#main_floor_thermostat`, `#kitchen_settings_popup`
- Shared popups: `kohbo/shared/main_floor_vacuum_popup.yaml`

### Partials (Reusable Card Collections)
Card collections `!include`d into multiple pages. Not templates—they're specific card instances.
- Location: `kohbo/<section>/partials/` or `kohbo/rooms/partials/`
- Examples: `rooms/partials/main_floor_room_cards.yaml`
- Use when same cards appear in multiple views

### Decision Flow

```
Creating a new file in kohbo/?
│
├─► Is it a main nav item? → Put in <section>/<section>.yaml
│
├─► Is it a detail/room page? → Put in <section>/<page>.yaml with subview: true
│
├─► Is it a popup used by multiple pages? → Put in kohbo/shared/
│
├─► Is it a popup used by one page? → Define inline in that page
│
└─► Is it a card collection to reuse? → Put in <section>/partials/
```

