## Theme Colors Reference

**REQUIRED: Always use CSS variables from the theme, never hardcode hex colors.**

The theme file defines all colors: `themes/kohbo/kohbo.yaml`

**Benefits:**
- Consistency across all dashboards
- Easy theme-wide color changes
- Maintains design system integrity

**Common theme variables:**

| Variable | Use For | Theme Value |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `var(--primary-color)` | Active states, primary accent | #59A5D8 |
| `var(--accent-color)` | Warnings, highlights | #FFD166 |
| `var(--success-color)` | Success states | #06D6A0 |
| `var(--error-color)` | Errors, alerts | #ED4747 |
| `var(--orange-color)` | High/caution states | #E36001 |
| `var(--light-grey-color)` | Inactive states | #ADB5BD |
| `var(--primary-text-color)` | Main text | #F8F9FA |
| `var(--secondary-text-color)` | Secondary text | #CED4DA |
| `var(--dark-primary-color)` | Card backgrounds | #343A40 |
| `var(--darker-primary-color)` | Secondary backgrounds | #2D3339 |
| `var(--divider-color)` | Borders, dividers | #495057 |

**Examples:**

```yaml
# ✅ CORRECT - Use CSS variables
color_thresholds:
  - color: var(--success-color)
    value: 100
  - color: var(--accent-color)
    value: 500
  - color: var(--error-color)
    value: 1000

# ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded hex values
color_thresholds:
  - color: "#06D6A0"
    value: 100
  - color: "#FFD166"
    value: 500
  - color: "#ED4747"
    value: 1000
```

**Works in:**
- `mini-graph-card` color_thresholds
- `button-card` styles (CSS properties)
- `card_mod` styles
- JavaScript templates returning color strings

